/* INTERVIEW QUESTIONS

In this editor window, I want you to demonstate the following:

Everytime a user clicks on the Change Color Button, I want you to change the background of the body tag to a random color using on Javascript

You are allowed to use jQuery or any other library you wish.

Your code will be reviewed on the following criteria:
1. Does it do what it is supposed to do?
2. How simple is it?
3. If the requirement changes, how easy will it be for someone else to jump in and change the code?


When you are done, please click save and send us the new link to your jsfiddle code

*/

var colors = ["#3c6ac95", "#ffd966", "#6aa84f", "#cc0000"];


$(".colour").click(function() {
  var rand = Math.floor(Math.random() * colors.length);
  $("body").css("background-color", colors[rand]);
})
